ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version
0 = neither; 1 = right; 2 = left; 3 = bilateral; blank = Missing Form/Incomplete Workbook

ElementDescription: Incomplete delineation of medial compartment - some JSW(x) set to .T
Medial JSW(x) cannot be measured due to poor positioning or poor image quality
Medial mJSW cannot be measured due to poor positioning, image quality or other reason
Medial mJSW measured but there is no local minimum
mJSW is set to zero, used when reader judges bone on bone in medial compartment
Distance from tibial plateau to tibial rim closest to femoral condyle (mm)
Pixel size used for conversion from pixel units to millimeters (uncorrected for magnification of knee) (mm)
X-ray beam angle from Synaflexer phantom (degrees)
Inconsistent positioning at one or more visits based on rim distance
Width of femoral condyles used to define x=1.0 (mm)
Lateral JSW(x) cannot be measured due to poor positioning or poor image quality
Lateral tibial plateau margin is the same as the bone edge
Incomplete delineation of lateral compartment - some JSW(x) set to .T
